                          Fronttalk Separators:
                         Date Separator Formats 

For general information about separators see "HELP SEP".  The %t and %d
item functions and the %o and %N conference functions print dates and times.
The format used can be specified by giving a number prefix, like '%3t'.
The following formats are understood:

   CODE  DESCRIPTION               EXAMPLE
    0    full date/time            Wed Feb 16 13:26:14 2002
    1    full date/time            Wed, Feb 16, 2002 (13:26)
    2    weekday                   Wed
    3    month abbreviation        Feb
    4    day of month              16
    5    2-digit year              02
    6    4-digit year              2002
    7    24-hour hour              13
    8    minutes                   26
    9    seconds                   14
   10    12-hour hour              1
   11    am or pm                  pm
   12    AM or PM                  PM
   13    month number              2
   14    day of year (001 to 366)  047
   15    day or week (0 - 6)       3

If no code is given, %d defaults to 1 and the others default to 0.
